#Quick start for Linux PXE Boot server - Cobbler

## I like this site - https://www.linuxtechi.com/install-and-configure-cobbler-on-centos-7/

# Install first
- yum install cobbler
- yum install cobbler_web

- also install:
- 

# Call outs
- systemctl restart cobblerd
- cobbler check 
- when the ins say to edit the DHCP file, they really mean the dhcp.template file

# vi /etc/cobbler/settings
-------------------------------------------------------
manage_dhcp: 1
manage_dns: 1
pxe_just_once: 1
